 Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":0,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Strangways was born in 1382, in Winton, Yorkshire, England as the daughter of Henry Strangways. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir Thomas Mountfort. She died in 1421, at the age of 39."},"et":{"1382–1421":"1382–1421","1382–1442":"1382–1442","1382–Female":"1382–Surnud","1384–Female":"1384–Surnud","1386–Male":"1386–Surnud","1390–Male":"1390–Surnud","1392–Female":"1392–Surnud","1396–Male":"1396–Surnud","1398–Female":"1398–Surnud","1380–1435":"1380–1435","1405–1462":"1405–1462","1356–1429":"1356–1429","1462":"1462","1396":"1396","1384":"1384","1382":"1382","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1435":"1435","1356":"1356","1421":"1421","1398":"1398","1442":"1442","1386":"1386","1429":"1429","1405":"1405","Winton, Yorkshire, England":"Winton, Yorkshire, England","Box, Wiltshire, England":"Box, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1382–1421":"1382–1421","1382–1442":"1382–1442","1382–Female":"1382–Kuollut","1384–Female":"1384–Kuollut","1386–Male":"1386–Kuollut","1390–Male":"1390–Kuollut","1392–Female":"1392–Kuollut","1396–Male":"1396–Kuollut","1398–Female":"1398–Kuollut","1380–1435":"1380–1435","1405–1462":"1405–1462","1356–1429":"1356–1429","1462":"1462","1396":"1396","1384":"1384","1382":"1382",